== Challenges ==

A feature which lets you complete challenges<ref>`Complete!` `When the player completes all their challenges` [https://crowdin.com/editor/vrchat-application/19#130850 Crowdin]</ref><ref>`All Challenges Completed!` `When the player completes all their assigned challenges` [https://crowdin.com/editor/vrchat-application/19#130854 Crowdin]</ref>. First discovery on December 13, 2024. Last new discovery on December 16, 2024. This feature is not yet accessible to all users, and seems to only be available for some VRChat accounts.

Challenges:
* Make X Friends<ref>`Make {0} Friends`, `A challenge for players to make {0} number of friends.` - [https://crowdin.com/editor/vrchat-application/19#130852 Crowdin]</ref>
* Visit X Friends<ref>`Visit {0} Worlds`, `Challenge description: When a player visit X number of worlds.` - [https://crowdin.com/editor/vrchat-application/19#130860 Crowdin]</ref>
* Visit X Worlds<ref name="crowdin130860">`Visit {0} Worlds`, `Challenge description: When a player visit X number of worlds.` - [https://crowdin.com/editor/vrchat-application/19#130860 Crowdin]</ref>
* Try VRChat on Another Platform<ref>`Try VRChat on Another Platform`, `Challenge description: When a player plays VRC on another platform` - [https://crowdin.com/editor/vrchat-application/19#130856 Crowdin]</ref>
* Log in X Days in a Row<ref>`Log in {0} Days in a Row`, `Challenge description: When a player logs in X number of days in a row.` - [https://crowdin.com/editor/vrchat-application/19#130858 Crowdin]</ref>

== ToxMod ==
ToxMod is an AI-assisted voice chat moderation product made by Modulate, intended to detect and flag toxic or abusive voice behavior.

In 2022 ToxMod got partially integrated. VRChat later stated that the team had previously been in discussions with Modulate, and that VRChat was inadvertently listed as a ToxMod customer<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20220424073126/https://www.modulate.ai/ modulate.ai from 2022] at archive.org</ref>, but that VRChat has no current or future plans to implement ToxMod<ref>[https://ask.vrchat.com/t/developer-update-1-december-2022/15263?page=3#p-30487-toxicity-in-vrchat-15 VRChat Blog Post]</ref>.

== Discord Social SDK ==

VRChat is implementing [https://discord.com/developers/social-sdk Discord Social SDK], which allows users to interact with there Discord friends on VRChat. This includes Invites, Joining, Friending, Unfriending. So far no indications to send messages, calls, or screen sharing/streaming. This feature can be disabled in the Settings<ref>'You can now invite and add your friends from Discord via VRChat! Not interested? Disable it via Settings!' - [https://crowdin.com/editor/vrchat-application/19/en-fr?view=comfortable#139887 Crowdin]</ref><ref>>'Allow Discord Friends' - [https://crowdin.com/editor/vrchat-application/19/en-fr?view=comfortable#139895 Crowdin]</ref>.

== Instance avatar performance requirements ==
[[File:Group permission - Bypass avatar performance requirements.png|thumb]]
A new group permission on the website in group role settings has been spotted:

{{Quote|
'''''Bypass Avatar Performance Requirements'''''

''Allows role to join group instances that have a minimum avatar performance requirement, regardless of their avatar's performance rating.''}}

This seems to suggest a feature might be implemented in the future allowing instances to have a minimum avatar performance requirement set in place.

